    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>No. 173 
                    The British Embassy to the Department of State</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1945Berlinv01</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d173</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">173</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1945-06-28T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1945-06-28T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-06-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-06-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="173" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d173">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">860f.4016/6–2845</note>
                <head>No. 173 <lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">British Embassy</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Department of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Extract]<note n="1" xml:id="d173fn1">For the full text
                            of this message, see <ref target="#d437">document No. 437</ref>.</note>
                    </seg>
                </opener>
                <p rend="flushleft">Ref: 512/15/45</p>
                <p rend="center">
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paraphrase of Telegram From Foreign Office to Washington
                        Dated June</hi> 22<hi rend="smallcaps">nd</hi>, 1945</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <p>3. It seems to us that a full exchange of views with the Americans on the whole
                    question of transfers of ethnic minority groups in Europe is desirable, … Such
                    an exchange of views might lead up to tripartite discussion on the subject at
                    the forthcoming meeting of the “Big Three”. Will you sound the State Department
                    on the latter proposal and let us know their reactions to it?</p>
                <p rend="center">. . . . . . .</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-06-28">June 28th,
                            1945</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
